title: For Sale:  7.62x54R Ammo 120 Round Assortment - All The Good Stuff
postcontent:
Here's an assortment of 7.62x54 ammo that's become hard to get these days.

40 rounds Hungarian Silver/Yellow tip. This ammo has a 182 grain steel core bullet.   
It hits much harder than the light ball that's currently available, and it penetrates like crazy.  
It also shoots a good deal more accurately in my rifles.

20 rounds East German M39 ammo. This ammo has an all black color 124 grain steel jacketed, steel core bullet. It was originally designed as practice ammo for their machine guns. The concept was that the lighter bullet would travel less far. It is however a full power round and will penetrate 1/4" steel plate at 100 yards. Recoil is greatly reduced due to the lighter bullet making it perfect for anyone who is sensitive to recoil.   

20 rounds Bulgarian brass case with a 149 grain magnetic bullet. Ammo is from the mid 50's but looks like it was made yesterday. It's super clean ammo and I've always felt brass cased ammo operated more smoothly than the steel case stuff.

20 rounds Red Tracer loaded on 4 Mosin stripper clips. Trace lights around 100 yards and continues another 700 - 800 yards. Visible in daylight but spectacular in low light conditions.

20 rounds Green Tracer. Very similar to the red tracer above except burn color is green. It's also packed on 4 Mosin stripper clips.

$120 picked up in the Brandon area. You must be at least 18 to purchase.
